  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nRunning lodestar beacon command breaks with\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ ./packages/cli/bin/lodestar.js beacon\r\n âœ– TypeError: The \"path\" argument must be of type string. Received undefined\r\n    at new NodeError (node:internal/errors:372:5)\r\n    at validateString (node:internal/validators:120:11)\r\n    at Object.join (node:path:1172:7)\r\n    at getCliLogger (file:///home/lion/Code/eth2.0/lodestar/packages/cli/src/util/logger.ts:75:43)\r\n    at Object.beaconHandler [as handler] (file:///home/lion/Code/eth2.0/lodestar/packages/cli/src/cmds/beacon/handler.ts:32:18)\r\n```\r\n\r\n- The regression was introduced here https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/4538\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/7ec526a34beedc773d99cd372b380de47afdd529/packages/cli/src/cmds/beacon/handler.ts#L32\r\n\r\n`args` is typed with `dataDir` property being a non-optional string. However, the object generated by Yargs may not include that property.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nIf `dataDir` can be undefined, it must typed as such",
